message.body: Gummy life savers for breakfast. Breakfast of champions!
I haven't had those in so long. That's a pretty yummy breakfast!
Now I'm having a grown-up breakfast lol. How was last night?

Ohhh what kind of grown up breakfast? It was good, the food was tasty. It's becoming a pattern that I get home recently at night? Get changed, and accidentally fall asleep without doing my nightly routine (which is not good). I then wake up earlier than expecting and try to get myself to fall back asleep. I woke up around 7 something this morning and successfully went back to sleep. I woke up at 8 something yesterday and didn't and that why I got tired pretty early last night.
What's happening to me???
You're getting into the office routine lol and getting used to a somewhat normal sleep cycle
Coffee, eggs, 2 sausage links, and home fries. 1.75 at Ikea! Lol I didn't go yesterday
I was going to ask how was IKEA yesterday but now I know. Nice. I have a hankering for French toast at the moment.
Easy to make!
You have bread eggs cinnamon vanilla extract and butter?
Nope.
Plus, I donning trust myself making it right now hahah.
I would walk you through it lol. Oh well. Guess you'll stay hungry for now
I'm actually good for now. Did you get your furniture?
Did not. Decided to wait for dryer weather
Guess what I'm having?
ï¿¼
A cow?!
Yummy! :)
And why a cow may I ask?
Bart Simpson. Don't have a cow, man!
Don't watch the Simpsons.
That's where it came from.
I believe you.
I ate so much earlier that I'm just feeling lethargic.
I don't like that feeling lol. Gotta loosen up the pants
How's bowling?
We didn't go. The lanes were all taken then Cindy had you work
Oh that sucks.
Soooo whatcha doing this Saturday? Would you wanna be my +1 for a wedding?

Steve, are you kidding me?! Remember how Uyen worked at SGH before she left? Well she needed someone to cover for her now so she asked me, and I said I would. I literally just told the manager on Thursday that I would do it this upcoming weekend!
Did you just find out about the wedding?
I have stellar timing lol
No. I forgot how close it was... The date kinda snuck up on me
Yes you do! Who's getting married?
A friend from when I grew up
Where's the wedding?
Ocean city restaurant
Oh that's where my eldest sister had her reception.
It's a nice place. Yeah, why not.
So that's a definite no then?
Yea, I'm sorry. I already told them I could be there.
Don't be. It's my own bad timing.
How was your day? Did you get seconds at bambu?
I hope you have fun! Get some cake.
Ohhhhh no way!

So we went to eat first. I ate way too much and pretty much gorged. By the time we got to Bambu, I was so full and had to slowly sip my #10 (btw, my friends really like my drink)! I was feeling full and lethargic for hours. Even walking around Center City didn't help make it go away. Even by the time we went to dinner, I was the only one to not get anything. I was just sipping water because I was still full!
I'm currently having heartburn.
Lunch man...
Oh dear. You went buffet more extreme lol
Mode*
You know you are a hard lady to schedule with. Always in demand of!
It wasn't even a buffet! It was just my first meal of the day because i waited to go out with everyone, I was hungry, and the food was delicious.
You should always know to prime yourself lol. I figured you would've known since you'd be with them all day.
I don't think so. I think it's that things just happen to fall on the same weekends or clusters of days for me. Also, I babysit.
You're right haha. Speaking of dates coming up fast. My Milan trip is up in just over a month. My sister is doing hardcore planning. She has three spreadsheets to share with me.
I think it's reasonable to expect my food to digest throughout the day.
It just stuck with me longer today.
There's one for gear to pack, our itinerary, and tips/training (ie learning some Italian)
Whoa, she's not messing around.
Lol yes it is but not when you're so lethargic. I kinda hope that doesn't happen when I go to Italy. It's gonna be awesome.
Hopefully not, bring antacids just in case.
It will be! It's Italy.
We might need those actually. Sister and I are prone to heart burn thanks to our father and his genes lol
There you go! Make sure that's on the list.
This is unlikely and I may have asked already but do you watch walking dead?
No I don't.
Ah. Tonight's episode was brutal and I kinda wanted to discuss with someone.
That reminds me. We haven't been taking about our night owl shows and articles in a while
Did they kill off a main character?
Yeah although it was a new recruit it was a really good one...
Sucks for that actor.

Tigers cannot purr. To show happiness, tigers squint or close their eyes. This is because losing vision lowers defense, so tigers only purposefully do so when they feel comfortable and safe http://i.imgur.com/GleAY3f.jpg
Awwww that's so cute!
